<br>
And I kind of get pissed when I see people not following simple etiquette. These are the rules I personally live by when auctioning my wares, or looking for gear. <br>
<br>
1.) Put your prices in your auctions. Don't think this pulls the wool over anyones eyes. This makes YOU seem like you are out to get the best deal. If you are "taking offers" SAY THAT.<br>
If I see "WTS ItemX" And no price, or notice, I ask the person "How much do you want?"<br>
If they reply with "Make offer" They are attempting to make the best possible profit. If you want to take offers, say it, otherwise it is best you be left alone.<br>
<br>
2.)Lately I see "So and So auctions, ' ItemX! ' "<br>
They leave no WTS or WTB. This is lazy. Say WTS or BUYING. Makes it more clear, and it catches the attention of the people that are buying things. Which brings me to my 3rd point.<br>
<br>
3.) Don't use WTB. It looks too simalar to WTS. Instead, use "BUYING" It stands out much more, and it should catch the selling people's eye much better, yet it does not spam or put your whole auction in caps.<br>
<br>
4.) DON'T SELL BAGS OF GEAR. This is teidious (sp?) If you want to sell your gear, MAKE AN AUCTION. It becomes easier for YOU. People like simplicity, having to go find you, hail you, open a trade with you, is very complicated compaired to reading what you have to sell on your auction. There is no positive to this practice. Not only this, but there is a bug involved with the bags in trade windows. You put your bag in the window, if the server does not recognize that you have a trade open (extreme lag) The person on the other side of the trade does not see anything either, you cancel the trade, and your bag poofs as a result of the server. By petitioning, you will get your bag(s) back, but it is a hassle that has no reason to be there.<br>
<br>
5.) Don't ask to try things on. Yes, you may want to see what it looks like, but instead ask if you may buy it, and then trade back. If the person refuses to trade back after you have agreed to trade back, then by all means post them in the scammer section. If you want to try something on, and don't have the cash, give the person some insurance. (an item on you of equal value)<br>
<br>
6.) Trade back. If someone has a problem/doesn't want the item you have just sold them, or if they changed their mind about selling it to you. Trade back. It is a nice gesture, and flat out rude to refuse the trade back. <br>
<br>
7,) If you are buying gear to make a profit, don't sell the gear you bought until after the seller has left the zone. <br>
I.E. You buy a Fungi Tunic for 20k so you can re-auction it at 30k, do not start auctioning it until the person who sold it to you has left the zone. <br>
It's rude to auction it while they are there, and it appears as though you ripped them off. <br>
<br>
8.) Last one I can think of. . . don't scam. Self explanatory!<br>
<br>
If anyone has any others, post them please. <p><center><table width=350 border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
